A company has decided to give a 12% discount to customers who have shopped for atleast Rs. 1000. Given the total MRP of goods purchased by a customer, return the bill amount of the customer (upto 3 decimal places).

Input Format

A single number (in double) representing MRP.

Constraints

None

Output Format

A single number (in double) representing the total bill amount.

Sample Input 0

345
Sample Output 0

345.000
Explanation 0

No discount for customers purchasing goods worth less than Rs. 1000

import java.util.*;
import java.io.*;
public class main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Scanner scn = new Scanner (System.in);
         double mrp = scn.nextDouble();
         if(mrp>=1000){
            mrp -= 0.12*mrp;

         }
         System.out.println("%.3f",mrp);
        }
        }